l\";s:25:\"title-font-letter-spacing\";s:3:\"0px\";s:20:\"title-font-uppercase\";s:7:\"disable\";s:17:\"caption-font-size\";s:4:\"16px\";s:19:\"caption-font-weight\";s:3:\"400\";s:18:\"caption-font-style\";s:6:\"italic\";s:27:\"caption-font-letter-spacing\";s:3:\"0px\";s:22:\"caption-font-uppercase\";s:7:\"disable\";s:15:\"left-icon-color\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"title-color\";s:0:\"\";s:22:\"title-link-hover-color\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"caption-color\";s:0:\"\";s:14:\"caption-spaces\";s:4:\"10px\";s:18:\"media-margin-right\";s:4:\"15px\";s:14:\"padding-bottom\";s:4:\"35px\";}}i:1;a:3:{s:8:\"template\";s:7:\"element\";s:4:\"type\";s:10:\"toggle-box\";s:5:\"value\";a:6:{s:2:\"id\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"class\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"tabs\";a:4:{i:0;a:4:{s:9:\"head-text\";s:5:\"Day 1\";s:5:\"title\";s:46:\"Transfer from Kampala/ to Bwindi National Park\";s:7:\"content\";s:444:\"On this first day of your gorilla trekking safari in Uganda, our tour guide will Transfer you from Entebbe/Kampala to the Gorilla Sanctuary of Bwindi national park with lunch en-route and then reaching in the evening to check in at your selected lodge Where you may either choose to relax for tomorrow\'s day-long gorilla trekking or take a self-guided walk around the Hotel. \n\nDinner and overnight at Buhoma Community Rest Camp or Buhoma Lodge.\";s:6:\"active\";s:6:\"enable\";}i:1;a:4:{s:9:\"head-text\";s:5:\"Day 2\";s:5:\"title\";s:17:\"Gorilla Trekking \";s:7:\"content\";s:783:\"After an early breakfast at 6.30am, with the help of our safari guide, you will depart to the park headquarters proceed for briefing by the park ranger guides before starting the Gorilla trek in the steep densely forested and beautiful landscape of Bwindi Impenetrable forest - the park has ever green vegetation which is also very thick due to the frequent rains throughout the year. The actual meaning of gorilla trekking is felt when you encounter with these giant but very gentle Mountain gorillas. \n\nIt\'s such the best and amazing experience to Watch Gorillas feed, rest, mothers with babies and the acrobatic youths playing about. \nThis gives the true meaning of wildlife and the best wildlife experience ever! Dinner and overnight at Buhoma Community Rest Camp or Buhoma Lodge\";s:6:\"active\";s:6:\"enable\";}i:2;a:4:{s:9:\"head-text\";s:5:\"Day 3\";s:5:\"title\";s:53:\"Queen Elizabeth National for Game Drive & Boat Cruise\";s:7:\"content\";s:545:\"Wake up Early and transfer to Queen Elizabeth national park reaching early and check in at your hotel for lunch, after lunch you will go for the afternoon boat cruise on the Kazinga Channel which is an interesting experience. Variety of animals a viewed while on boat include different bird life on water which include the African skimmer, jacana, rare shoe bill among others .after enjoying the boat trip you will be transferred to your lodge with the help of our safari guide for dinner and overnight at Mweya Safari Lodge or Simba Safari Camp\";s:6:\"active\";s:6:\"enable\";}i:3;a:4:{s:9:\"head-text\";s:5:\"Day 4\";s:5:\"title\";s:16:\"Back to Kampala.\";s:7:\"content\";s:575:\"At 6:30 a.m. in the morning, you will leave for game drive, this is the best time to spot hyenas, lions, leopards, giant forest hogs, hippos coming back to the rivers, huge herds of buffaloes and elephants, Ugandan Kobs and crested cranes among others and then return to your lodge for late breakfast and get you packed lunch to enjoy en-route. \n\nTransfer back to Kampala as you end your 4 days gorilla and wildlife safari in Uganda viewing game en-route with a stopover in Fort Portal or Mubende for your lunch and finally drive to Kampala to catch up your flight back home.\";s:6:\"active\";s:6:\"enable\";}}s:5:\"style\";s:16:\"background-title\";s:5:\"align\";s:4:\"left\";s:14:\"padding-bottom\";s:4:\"25px\";}}i:2;a:3:{s:8:\"template\";s:7:\"element\";s:4:\"type\";s:7:\"divider\";s:5:\"value\";a:14:{s:2:\"id\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"class\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"normal\";s:9:\"icon-type\";s:4:\"