:\"icon\";s:9:\"left-icon\";s:9:\"fa fa-bus\";s:10:\"left-image\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"heading-tag\";s:2:\"h6\";s:14:\"icon-font-size\";s:4:\"18px\";s:15:\"title-font-size\";s:4:\"24px\";s:17:\"title-font-weight\";s:3:\"600\";s:16:\"title-font-style\";s:6:\"normal\";s:25:\"title-font-letter-spacing\";s:3:\"0px\";s:20:\"title-font-uppercase\";s:7:\"disable\";s:17:\"caption-font-size\";s:4:\"16px\";s:19:\"caption-font-weight\";s:3:\"400\";s:18:\"caption-font-style\";s:6:\"italic\";s:27:\"caption-font-letter-spacing\";s:3:\"0px\";s:22:\"caption-font-uppercase\";s:7:\"disable\";s:15:\"left-icon-color\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"title-color\";s:0:\"\";s:22:\"title-link-hover-color\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"caption-color\";s:0:\"\";s:14:\"caption-spaces\";s:4:\"10px\";s:18:\"media-margin-right\";s:4:\"15px\";s:14:\"padding-bottom\";s:4:\"35px\";}}i:1;a:3:{s:8:\"template\";s:7:\"element\";s:4:\"type\";s:10:\"toggle-box\";s:5:\"value\";a:6:{s:2:\"id\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"class\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"tabs\";a:8:{i:0;a:4:{s:9:\"head-text\";s:5:\"Day 1\";s:5:\"title\";s:39:\"Airport transfer and arrival at Entebbe\";s:7:\"content\";s:116:\"Our professional guide meet up with your and drive you to your Hotel in Kampala or Entebbe for overnight and dinner.\";s:6:\"active\";s:6:\"enable\";}i:1;a:4:{s:9:\"head-text\";s:5:\"Day 2\";s:5:\"title\";s:55:\"Depart Kampala and transfer to Lake Mburo National park\";s:7:\"content\";s:390:\"Rise up Early to kick-start your safari by traveling from Kampala through the Equator proceed South-westwards and arrive at Lake Mburo in the afternoon, check into your choice of accommodation. \n\nTake an evening game drive and encounter zebras, buffalo, elands and impalas along with a great variety of birds. Overnight and dinner at Rwonyo Rest Camp (Budget) or Arcadia Cottages (Upmarket)\";s:6:\"active\";s:6:\"enable\";}i:2;a:4:{s:9:\"head-text\";s:5:\"Day 3\";s:5:\"title\";s:41:\"Nature walk and Launch trip on Lake Mburo\";s:7:\"content\";s:814:\"After breakfast go for a guided nature walk on the western side of the lake begin at 7am and take two hours. At this time of day, you may encounter hyenas returning to their dens and hippos retreating to the lake. \n\nHikes through the woodland provide an opportunity to sight forest birds and mammals, while the walk to the top of the hill rewards visitors with a spectacular view of 9 of the region’s 14 lakes come back to your Lodge for Lunch. \n\nIn afternoon take a tranquil evening boat ride along the eastern banks of Lake Mburo. Keep an eye out for crocodiles, buffaloes and hippos as well as colorful Kingfishers, magnificent Fish Eagles, Hammerkops and their enormous nests and even the prehistoric-looking Shoebill against the setting Sun .Night at Rwonyo Rest Camp (Budget) or Arcadia Cottages (Upmarket)\";s:6:\"active\";s:6:\"enable\";}i:3;a:4:{s:9:\"head-text\";s:5:\"Day 4\";s:5:\"title\";s:41:\"Transfer to Queen Elizabeth national park\";s:7:\"content\";s:491:\"Have a cup of coffee in the morning, and after drive to Queen Elizabeth national park, this journey will take you through the historical Kasese town with the clear view of the mountains of the moon. \n\nYou will also enjoy a game drive on your way to the accommodation facility in the middle of the park which provides a chance to spot many animals like waterbucks, warthogs and other wildlife. \n\nEvening is at your own leisure Dinner and overnight at Simba Safari Camp or Mweya safari Lodge.\n\";s:6:\"active\";s:6:\"enable\";}i:4;a:4:{s:9:\"head-text\";s:5:\"Day 5\";s:5:\"title\";s:29:\"Queen Elizabeth national park\";s:7:\"content\";s:593:\"You will begin with a game drive in the morning towards the mating grounds of the Kobs, we look for the great residents of the park, and these include the lions, elephants, buffaloes and early risers, before transferring at the lodge for lunch.  After having your lunch, you will proceed to Kazinga channel to take a boat cruise. \n\nIts shores attract a large number of birdlife, mammals and reptiles year around. The boat cruise on Kazinga channel is a must visit for all tourists visiting Queen Elizabeth National Park. Dinner and overnight at budget Simba Safari Camp or Mweya safari Lodge. \";s:6:\"active\";s:6:\"enable\";}i:5;a:4:{s:9:\"head-text\";s:5:\"Day 6\";s:5:\"title\";s:39:\"Transfer to Kibale Forest national park\";s:7:\"content\";s:265:\"This Morning after breakfast, you will be transferred to Kibale forest national park for chimpanzee trekking. You will have a lunch stopover before continuing to your lodge at the park where you will have dinner and overnight at Primate Lodge or Kibale Forest Camp \";s:6:\"active\";s:6:\"enable\";}i:6;a:4:{s:9:\"head-text\";s:5:\"Day 7\";s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"Chimpanzee trekking\";s:7:\"content\";s:468:\"After early your guide will drive you to Kanyanchu Tourist center for briefing before going for chimpanzee tracking tour. These apes are more closely related to humans that to any other creatures. Kibale National Forest is well known for its unique primates in East Africa. On the walk you will go through this tropical moist forest to find the chimpanzee. After having your lunch, optional Bigodi swamp walk or relax at your hotel. Primate Lodge or Kibale Forest Camp\";s:6:\"active\";s:6:\"enable\";}i:7;a:4:{s:9:\"head-text\";s:5:\"Day 8\";s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"Transfer back to Kampala\";s:7:\"content\";s:146:\"Drive around fort portal Tooro Kingdom and Tea leaves estate before embarking to your return trip to Kampala through Mubende.\n***End of Safari***\n\";s:6:\"active\";s:6:\"enable\";}}s:5:\"style\";s:8:\"box-icon\";s:5:\"align\";s:4:\"left\";s:14:\"padding-bottom\";s:4:\"25px\";}}i:2;a:3:{s:8:\"template\";s:7:\"element\";s:4:\"type\";s:7:\"divider\";s:5:\"value\";a:14:{s:2:\"id\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"class\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"normal\";s:9:\"icon-type\";s:4:\"icon\";s:5:\"image\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"icon\";s:10:\"fa fa-film\";s:5:\"style\";s:5:\"solid\";s:5:\"align\";s:6:\"center\";s:9:\"icon-size\";s:4:\"15px\";s:12:\"divide